This is the retired Chinese woman who has spent every day for 14 years swatting flies.

Ruan Tang, 80, from the Changmingsixiang Community in eastern China's Hangzhou City, has dedicated eight hours a day, seven days a week, to killing the pest.

She estimates that she can kill about 
1,000 flies a day, sometimes sitting by a litter bin for two hours at a 
time to make sure that she has got all the flies hiding inside.

