The local newspaper concluded: 'She manages to kill them in an environmentally friendly way, who knows how many flies there would be in the area if she was not in action.'

She told local television: 'I feel it is a great honour to help neighbours to wipe out disgusting flies. It is also great to have a meaningful role me to do so in my age, and it helps me to keep fit.'

Neighbour Jian Hsiao, 58, added: 'She is really a fly killing specialist, she is our heroine.

'Just imagine how many of these pesty insects would be there if she had not been wiping so many out every day.'

 

